    "updated_at": "2014-01-10T05:19:50Z",
    "body": "One problem is that the `ctypes` lint currently allows all non-C-like enums, which was basically a compromise to get the enum discriminant size patches to finally land.  If we can fix that \u2014 require an FFI-safe discriminant, or being a single-field nullable of an otherwise FFI-safe type, and I think that's it \u2014 then that would flag using `Option<i32>` or whatever in FFI.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
